Bellway, Dixons, Tullow Oil: U.K., Irish Equity Market Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-03-30T06:45:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/bellway-bp-plc-ifg-group-u-k-irish-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index (UKX)  rose 27.68 points, or 0.5
percent, to 5,932.17. The  FTSE All-Share Index (ASX)  gained 0.4
percent while Ireland’s ISEQ Index fell 1 percent.  Bellway Plc (BWY)  : The U.K. homebuilder specializing in
first-time buyers said first-half profit rose after the company
sold more homes at higher prices. The shares dropped 1.7 percent
to 682 pence.  BP Plc (BP/)  : Iain Conn, head of BP’s refining and
marketing unit, said the company is committed to resolving
issues with its TNK-BP partners over the proposed exploration
deal with OAO Rosneft. The shares retreated 2.2 percent to
466.55 pence.  Dixons Retail Plc (DXNS)  : The U.K’s largest consumer-
electronics retailer said full-year earnings will miss most
analysts’ estimates as sales decline because of weakening
consumer confidence. The shares rose 0.8 percent to 16.75 pence.  Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  : The company sold stakes in Ugandan
exploration blocks to Total SA and China National Offshore Oil
Corp. for $2.9 billion, paving the way for the development of
the Lake Albert Basin after the deal was held up by a tax
dispute. The shares rose 1.9 percent to 1,444 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
